	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=92743><span id= >Shimor</span></a><br><span id=notbold>30 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.91]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Okay, my warrior has soloed for about 80% of his career, and is still soloing at level 42. With validus custodus armor and centi SS, you can solo without upgrades until the mid 20's. Get to level 8 however you can, be it through the frog newbie zone, or quests, but get 8 fast. Then head to paludal caverns. Yes, it's over-camped, but usually only at the bandits. To start off, you want to zone in from the shadeweavers thicket side and kill anything blue or even. Move farther and farther in as you level, but avoid the fungoids. (They have a nasty disease proc) When you hit 12 or 13 and get dual wield, you want to move to the hollowshade moor side of the zone, where you can solo to 18 or 19. Then you will have to find a group at a bandit camp near Shadowhaven until level 24 or 25. Going from 8 to 24 usually takes me a total of 10 to 12 hours with a twinked melee character. Be sure to keep bind wound up, or go for a fungi/iksar bp, as cash permits. Iksar bp should be fine for regen until 30 or so. Once youve maxed out in paludal, it's time to upgrade your gear. A haste item is essential, go for SCHW if you can, they'll last you til 50. A wurmslayer or a good ratio two-hander is also necesary after 20 when the damage cap comes off. Don't neglect your 2hb skill, a Sarnak Battlehammer (30dmg 40dly war only) goes for 50-100pp in the bazaar and is a great weapon. Other items you'll need are plat or velium fire wedding rings (5ac 55hp or 6ac 65hp) Also, start picking up crustacean armor, as well as other pieces with good AC and stamina or raw hp on them. Frogs start with high dex and agility, so dont worry about those stats. Try to get all 4 melee stats over 100, then get strength and stamina as high as you can without lowering dex/agi. <br>At 25, with your new gear, you can either group in highhold keep, or solo Osargen there. He's a named prisoner who you can kill easily until 28. After that, you can do the boring FM/OT/DL cycle until 50 or so, or you can go elsewhere and solo for better exp and cash. Places to solo at 28 are echo caverns, marus seru and sol a. These places should get you to 35 fairly quickly. Another gear upgrade might be needed at this point. Wurmy will still do more damage than any other one-hander for under 4kpp. <br>Level 35, few great solo places are dawnshroud peaks, thurgadin, great divide, and eastern wastes. In eastern wastes, get a partner and kill the orcs. You should be able to solo drakkel dire wolves in GD and raise your thurg faction. Around level 40, you'll want to solo tribal gatherers and scouts in dawnshroud. they hit like pansies and have low hp, perfect solo mobs. Theyll start to go light blue at 42, head back to eastern wastes and kill ulthorks and walruses along the northern coast until 45.<br>Throughout all these levels, be sure to keep at least 1hb/1hs/2hs and maybe piercing and 2hb maxed. Don't forget to train parry/riposte/disarm, and try to keep bind wound as high as you can. Thats as high as I am, I may post again with solo spots past 45.<br><br>Oh, and to all you who don't think warriors can solo- I'm getting 4 blues per hour at 42 in eastern wastes. Just pull a single ulthork, kill it, and repeat. I stay under 45% hp so i'm always berserk, it increases your dps quite a bit. At 42 I have 2200hp, 850ac, and 925atk. I lose roughly 10-15% health every fight, use maybe 5 bandaids after every fight. faster exp and better loot than dreadlands.<br><br>Neksnappa Bonecrusha<br>42 Troll Warrior<br>Steel Horsemen<br>The Nameless</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
